      <entry xml:id="entry_sar_1" n="1" xml:lang="os" abv:completeness="incomplete">
        <form xml:id="form_d1223e66" type="lemma" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><orth>sar!</orth></form>
        <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>saræ!</orth></form>
        <sense>
          <sense xml:id="sense_d1223e69">
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>горе</q>
            </abv:tr>
          </sense>
          <sense>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>vae!</q>
            </abv:tr>
          </sense>
        </sense>
        <note type="comment">; в формулах угрозы и проклятия</note>
        <re>
          <form type="lemma"><orth><oRef>sar</oRef> dæ kʼопа! <oRef>sar</oRef> dæ
            xæʒar!</orth></form>
          <sense>
            <sense>
              <tr xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict" xml:lang="ru">
                <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">горе твоему дому!</q>
              </tr>
            </sense>
            <sense>
              <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                <q>vае domo tuo!</q>
              </abv:tr>
            </sense>
          </sense>
        </re>
        <re>
          <form type="lemma"><orth><oRef>sar</oRef> dæ sær!</orth></form>
          <sense>
            <tr xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict" xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">горе твоей голове!</q>
            </tr>
          </sense>
        </re>
        <exampleGrp xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">ew sæ kʼопа æmæ <oRef>sar</oRef> sæ
              xæʒar!</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">гибель их очагу и горе их дому!</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ИАА"/>
              <biblScope>II 276</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">majræmbony х˳zсaw dæ baxīzæd dæ xæʒaræj æddæ
              bazzajyn; wæd dodoj æmæ <oRef>sar</oRef> dæ sær kodta</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">в пятницу избави боже остаться вне своего дома;
                тогда беда и горе твоей голове!</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/>
              <biblScope>73</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
          <example>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">dodoj, <oRef>sar</oRef> туп jæ īid, ḱī mæ
              хопа wæjjagf</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">беда, горе тому (<q>душе того</q>), кто назовет
                меня рабом!</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Niger"/>
              <biblScope>108</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
          <example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
            <usg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><lang/></usg>
            <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><oRef xml:lang="os-x-digor">saræ</oRef> kænaj
              sæ kʼoпа!</quote>
            <tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">горе их дому!</q>
            </tr>
            <bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Qazb."/>
              <biblScope>51</biblScope></bibl>
          </example>
        </exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w type="rec"
              >sādram!</w>
            <gloss><q>горе</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>vae!</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>sār</w>
            <gloss><q>горе</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>огорчение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
            <w>sādra-</w><gloss><q>горе</q></gloss> в формулах проклятия: <note type="comment"
                ><example xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
                <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> sādram ahmāt naire!</quote>
                <tr xml:lang="ru">
                  <q xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">горе тому мужу!</q>
                </tr>
              </example></note>).</mentioned> В осетинском ожидали бы <mentioned xml:lang="os"><w
              type="rec">sard</w></mentioned> (группа <c>-rd</c> в исходе удерживается, ср. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_wyrd_1"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kard"/>, <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_mard"/> и др.). Однако в сочетании <mentioned xml:lang="os"
              ><note type="comment"><example xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
                <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">sard dæ</quote>
              </example></note></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><note
              type="comment">
              <example xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
                <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="rec">*sādram tai</quote>
              </example></note></mentioned>) легко могло произойти упрощение: <mentioned
            xml:lang="os"><note type="comment"><example
                xmlns="http://ossetic-studies.org/ns/abaevdict">
                <quote xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">sar dæ</quote>
              </example></note></mentioned>... Старую аланскую форму отражает, возможно, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
            <w>sardam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bbl"><lang/>
            <w>sart</w>
            <gloss><q>проклятие</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
      </entry>
